{"id":4888,"global_id":"www.unitingnc.org?id=4888","global_id_lineage":["www.unitingnc.org?id=4888"],"author":"25","status":"publish","date":"2019-03-28 11:29:53","date_utc":"2019-03-28 15:29:53","modified":"2019-03-28 11:29:53","modified_utc":"2019-03-28 15:29:53","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/stand-with-us\/april-28-faith-and-conscience-convocation-a-call-for-accountability-asheville\/","rest_url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-json\/tribe\/events\/v1\/events\/4888","title":"April 28: Faith and Conscience Convocation: A Call for Accountability (Asheville)","description":"<p>The convocation will explore North Carolina\u2019s connection, through the use of its public airports, a local airline (Aero Contractors), and locally based employees of the airline, to the CIA\u2019s Rendition, Detention, and Interrogation (RDI) program that began after the 9\/11 attacks. Muslim people were kidnapped, bound, and transported to CIA black sites and to foreign countries, where they were held indefinitely without charges and were tortured. Most were innocent of any offense.<\/p>\n<p>Speakers will include NC Commission of Inquiry on Torture Commissioner David Crane, former war crimes prosecutor, retired Colonel Larry Wilkerson who has extensive knowledge of the program, and Christina Cowger, a founder of NC Stop Torture Now.<\/p>\n<p>Deadline to register is April 25. This event is free, but you must RSVP on our website: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ncchurches.org\/event-single\/faith-and-conscience-convocation-a-call-for-accountability-for-torture\/?fbclid=IwAR2gahFeYoRFJQfMr_KF3w-u1pUXT65PSWbhPcnhSb93gOlRtO9ISbw60MI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https:\/\/l.facebook.com\/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncchurches.org%2Fevent-single%2Ffaith-and-conscience-convocation-a-call-for-accountability-for-torture%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2gahFeYoRFJQfMr_KF3w-u1pUXT65PSWbhPcnhSb93gOlRtO9ISbw60MI&amp;h=AT0T1siTWDF63XT-fl4ENV9Yz29hoZaQi